  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nAdding `charset` header in a request results in incorrect error for some REST API requests, e.g.:\r\n\r\nRequests:\r\n`curl -X GET http://<BEACON_IP>:4000/eth/v2/beacon/blocks/head -H \"Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8\" -H \"Accept: application/json; charset=utf-8\"`\r\n`curl -X GET http://<BEACON_IP>:4000/eth/v2/beacon/blocks/head -H \"Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8\" -H \"Accept: charset=utf-8\"`\r\nreturn error:\r\n`{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"BAD_REQUEST: Unsupported endpoint version: v2\",\"stacktraces\":[]}`\r\n\r\nWhile request:\r\n`curl -X GET http://<BEACON_IP>:4000/eth/v2/beacon/blocks/head -H \"Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8\" -H \"Accept: application/json\"`\r\n\r\nreturns no error and returns the head block successfully.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nDocker: sigp/lighthouse:latest-unstable\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\n`{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"BAD_REQUEST: Unsupported endpoint version: v2\",\"stacktraces\":[]}`\r\n\r\nIs not the correct response expected\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nBlock should be successfully returned regardless of the `charset` header.",
